Show Indian Database

The information contained in this database was compiled in 2010 by my research in the National Archives and Records in Kansas City, Missouri. All of the names contained in the database correspond to a signed contact between the performer and the Wild West in the presence of the Pine Ridge agent, mention of performers in correspondence and news articles, listings of performers in Wild West programs and route books, and government documentation. To the best of my knowledge, this is the first such listing of performers made available to researchers.

The database contains gaps in the data. At NARA Kansas City, the primary bulk of contracts exist after 1906. My research has dug up very few contracts for years prior to the twentieth century, although such contracts may exist at the National Archives in Washington, D.C.

Information in the table is sortable and can be rearranged by clicking on the table column headings.
